Values.Value: ::This computer's wiring is intuitively designed in such a way that it makes it quite clear as to which cable powers what section. There are a dozen of cords heading towards the destroyed tankers and a few more dedicated to operating the rest of the ship. It would be a waste of time attempting to reestablish the connection with the oil containers, so you shift your focus on fixing the rest of the stuff. After a few minutes you job is done and the console can be powered up once more.::
::Despite the device's clear and relatively simple design, the problem you're faced when it comes to repairing it is still too hard for you to solve.::
::Access granted, valves are now manually operable.::

::Cruise control.

Maneuvering thrusters offline. Missing readings from tanker sections 1-3.::
